  "text": "A second, but no less important reason to be interested in the light-like cusp anomalous dimension is the fact that it is a universal quantity that is ubiquitous in QFT computations. It appears for instance in the universal exponentiation of IR divergences in dimensional regularisation and gets its name from the computation of the light-like cusped Wilson line [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This function is usually mixed in with additional structure in a given scattering amplitude or form factor. The exception to this is the simplest, Sudakov form factor. This consists of a member of the stress-tensor multiplet (i.e. a local gauge invariant operator) and two members of the on-shell gluon multiplet that is unique in N = 4 SYM. This is a single-scale problem, and it can be shown that maximal supersymmetry factors off a universal tree-level form factor that contains all dependence on external polarizations as well as the dependence on the gluon color quantum numbers. Hence to any loop order",
