    "121225787": {
      "title": "Renormalization of the Wilson Loops Beyond the Leading Order",
      "abstract": "Abstract We study the renormalization properties of the Wilson loops containing cusp singularities. In particular, we calculate the two-loop contribution to the cusp anomalous dimension Γ cusp ( γ , g ) and investigate its behaviour in the limit of large and small cusp angles γ. The general form of Γ cusp ( γ , g ) is established in the limit of large minkowskian cusp angles γ, and the analyticity properties of Γ cusp with respect to γ are investigated. The relation of these results to the nonleading infrared behaviour of the quark form factor is demonstrated."
    },
    "119478846": {
      "title": "Loop Space Formalism and Renormalization Group for the Infrared Asymptotics of QCD",
      "abstract": "Abstract It is demonstrated that the IR asymptotics of an arbitrary hard process of perturbative QCD can be factorized out into the superposition of vacuum averages of path-ordered exponentials, the IR singularities of which are shown to be in a one-to-one correspondence with the UV ones, thus allowing one to apply renormalization group methods to study the IR asymptotics of perturbative QCD. The anomalous dimension Γ cusp of the relevant RG equation is calculated up to two loops."
    }
